Iowa Supreme Court upholds ban on felons voting The Iowa Supreme Court ruled 4-3 yesterday against an expansion of voting rights for convicted criminals, The Des Moines Register reports. There are about 56,500 Iowans disqualified from voting due to felony convictions, of which about 7,400 are currently in prison. Besides Iowa, only Florida and Kentucky bar convicted felons from voting unless they receive a restoration of rights from the governor.
